Abstra API

ProBroker

Version: 99.0.0.0.0

Generated date: 20230610

Introduction

The Abstra API is developed in order to give the ProBroker system the possibility to communicate with 3rd party clients. The development kit is available in C, C++, Java, DLL in Tcp/ip and XML in MQ. The document contains :

  • Detailed descriptions of Abstra requests. All items with name and datatype.
  • Description of RecordValue API.
  • Description of RecordDescriptor.
  • Technical descriptions regarding setup of the Abstra server.

Functionality in this API

The Abstra API is a transaction based interface to ProBroker. Theoretically, all the functionality that exists in ProBroker is accessible from Abstra, but currently only a subset of the transactions are available. This subset of transactions will be updated rapidly to satisfy 3rd party demands. Typical functionality is:

  • Registration and update of customer data
  • Get customer
  • Get instrument
  • Registration and update of orders
  • Order overview
  • Customer portifolio
  • Customer transactions

Identifying Customers

Customers are identified by the unique id IN_CUST_NO_SHORT. To extract this value you would have to perform a RQ_ABS_CUST_GET if you choose to not store this value in your own system.

Identifying Instruments

Instruments are identified by the unique primary key IN_INSTRUMENT_ID or the combination of 3 fields: IN_VP_NO, IN_ISO_CURR and IN_EXCH_ID (Isin, currency and primary exchange). To exctract the IN_INSTRUMENT_ID you would have to perform a RQ_ABS_VP_GET if you choose not to store this value in your system.

Architecture of the Abstra API

The ProBroker system has a client/server architecture. 3rd party clients is dealt with as any other clients. The Abstra server serves as a “protocolconverter” between extern API and ProBrokers own internal protocol.

Currencies and FX rates

There are three separate currency types that is used in ProBroker:

  • Currency - Settlement currency
  • Val Currency - Instrument's currency
  • Home Currency - System currency

Several fields come in these variants, typically prefixed by either _VAL_ or _HOME_ to indicate which currency it related to. As an example for the amount field:

  • IN_AMOUNT - Amount in settlement currency
  • IN_VAL_AMOUNT - Amount in instrument's currency
  • IN_HOME_AMOUNT - Amount in system currency

There exists several relations between these currencies:

  • Cross Rate - rate between instrument's currency and home currency. Cross rate = (Instrument Currency)/(Home Currency).
  • Forward Rate - rate between settlement currency and home currency. Forward rate = (Settlement Currency)/(Home Currency).
  • Val Rate - rate between settlement currency and instrument's currency. Val Rate = (Settlement Currency)/(Instruments Currency).

Customer requests

RQ_ABS_CUST_NEW

Back to top

Description:


Insert a new customer record.
Note:
If IN_INSTRUCTING_PARTY is provided then IN_TICKET_NOTIFICATION_OASYS is mandatory.
If IN_PASSPORT_EXPIRY_DATE is provided then IN_PASSPORT_NUMBER is mandatory.
If IN_MIFID_TYPE is not provided then MiFID Type defined on the CUST_GRP of the account will be used.

1) Collateral method Values and Description :
SICA: Securities financial collateral arrangement
SIUR: Securities financial with the right of use
TTCA: Title transfer collateral arrangement

2)If IN_LEI is provided then only IN_LEI_EXPIRY_DATE, IN_LEI_REGISTRATION_STATUS, IN_ENTITY_STATUS and IN_IS_BRANCH are acceptable.
If IN_IS_BRANCH is '1' then only IN_HEAD_OFFICE_LEI is acceptable.
If IN_HEAD_OFFICE_LEI is provided then only IN_HEAD_OFFICE_LEI_EXPIRY_DATE and IN_HEAD_OFFICE_LEI_COUNTRY_CODE are acceptable.
If IN_IS_BRANCH is blank then we are treating it as a 0 internally.
And when IN_IS_BRANCH is '0' then we are removing the head office LEI from customer as IN_HEAD_OFFICE_LEI is depends upon IN_IS_BRANCH.

3) If multiple risk classes allowed then risk classes should be passed using IN_SEPARATOR as shown below as an example:

R - In record descriptor

IN_SEPARATOR :'RISK_CLASS_LEVELS'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR
IN_ACCOUNT_RISK_CLASS_LEVEL : R
IN_SEPARATOR :'_GROUP_END_'
*The record descriptor (IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR) should only contain IN_ACCOUNT_RISK_CLASS_LEVEL field.

4) If there are more than 1 citizenships then those should be provided using IN_SEPARATOR as shown below as an example:

IN_SEPARATOR :'CUSTOMER_CITIZENSHIPS'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR
IN_COUNTRY_CODE : R
IN_PASSPORT_NUMBER : R
IN_PASSPORT_EXPIRY_DATE : R
IN_SEPARATOR :'_GROUP_END_'
*The record descriptor (IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR) will contain IN_COUNTRY_CODE, IN_PASSPORT_NUMBER, IN_PASSPORT_EXPIRY_DATE fields.

5) If there are more than one Investment reason then those should be provided using IN_SEPARATOR as shown below as an example:

IN_SEPARATOR : 'INVESTMENT_ADVICE_REASON_ID'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_REASON_ID : R
IN_SEPARATOR :'_GROUP_END_'
*The record descriptor (IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR) should only contain IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_REASON_ID field.

6) If there are more than one Customer identifiers then those should be provided using IN_SEPARATOR as shown below as an example:

IN_SEPARATOR :'CUSTOMER_IDENTIFIERS'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR
IN_CUSTOMER_IDENTIFIER_SOURCE_ID : R
IN_CUSTOMER_IDENTIFIER : R
IN_SEPARATOR : '_GROUP_END_'
*The record descriptor (IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR) should contain IN_CUSTOMER_IDENTIFIER_SOURCE_ID and IN_CUSTOMER_IDENTIFIER field.

RQ_ABS_CUST_GET

Back to top

Description:


Gets customer information and returns a list if more than one occurrence.
The list includes some additional fields if the setting GENERAL - REMOTE_CUST = 1 (These fields are marked with Y).

Explanation:
Y = In Record descriptor when the GENERAL setting REMOTE_CUST = 1

1) Account type should be passed using IN_SEPARATOR as shown below as an example:

IN_SEPARATOR :'ACCOUNT_TYPES'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR
IN_CUST_TYPE : R
IN_SEPARATOR :'_GROUP_END_'
*The record descriptor (IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR) should only contain IN_CUST_TYPE field.

2) Settlement currency should be passed using IN_SEPARATOR as shown below as an example:

IN_SEPARATOR :'CURRENCY'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR
IN_SETTLEMENT_CCY : R
IN_SEPARATOR :'_GROUP_END_'
*The record descriptor (IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR) should only contain IN_SETTLEMENT_CCY field.

3) MIFID type should be passed using IN_SEPARATOR as shown below as an example:

IN_SEPARATOR :'MIFID_TYPES'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR
IN_MIFID_TYPE : R
IN_SEPARATOR :'_GROUP_END_'
*The record descriptor (IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR) should only contain IN_MIFID_TYPE field.

4) Investment Type should be passed using IN_SEPARATOR as shown below as an example:

IN_SEPARATOR :'ACCOUNT_INVESTMENT_TYPES'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR
IN_ACCOUNT_INVESTMENT_TYPE : R
IN_SEPARATOR :'_GROUP_END_'
*The record descriptor (IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR) should only contain IN_ACCOUNT_INVESTMENT_TYPE field.

5) Client Type should be passed using IN_SEPARATOR as shown below as an example:

IN_SEPARATOR : 'CLIENT_TYPES'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR
IN_CLIENT_TYPE : R
IN_SEPARATOR :'_GROUP_END_'
*The record descriptor (IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR) should only contain IN_CLIENT_TYPE field.

5) Country Code should be passed using IN_SEPARATOR as shown below as an example:

IN_SEPARATOR :'COUNTRY_CODES'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR
IN_COUNTRY_CODE : R
IN_SEPARATOR :'_GROUP_END_'
*The record descriptor (IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR) should only contain IN_COUNTRY_CODE field.

RQ_ABS_CUST_CALC_COMMISSION

Back to top

Description:


Calculates commission for a combination of customer and instrument.

Note:
The estimated amount in IN_EST_AMOUNT is expected to be presented in the currency of the security traded, not in the home currency.
Also Estimated amount is optional to Limit as follow :
1) If Estimated amount and quantity are provided then Estimated amount is considered for calculations.
2) If Estimated amount is absent but quantity and limit present then (quantity * limit ) is used for calculation which is more accurate.
3) If quantity, limit and estimated amount are provided then I am considering (quantity * limit) amount provided.
B. IN_EST_AMOUNT, IN_ORDER_SOURCE Seems not to be mandatory in-param.

O1 = Mandatory if IN_INSTRUMENT_ID is not provided.



Input Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_CUST_NO_SHORT
XMandatory
Unique identifier for account in ProBroker.IT_CUST_NO_SHORTVarchar(16)
IN_ORDER_SOURCE
XMandatory

'NA' - N/A
'00' - ProBroker
'01' - IU
'02' - Maturity
'03' - Internet
'04' - Extern
'05' - Custody
'06' - First Issue
'07' - Model portfolio investment.		IT_CHARCODEVarchar(2)

O1		IT_ISIN_NOVarchar(12)

O1		IT_ISO_CURRVarchar(3)
IN_TS_EXCH_IDExchange Identifier. Defined by ISO-10383 Market Identifier Code.
O1		IT_TS_EXCH_IDVarchar(12)

Customer Requests - Taxation

RQ_ABS_CUST_TAXATION_NEW

Back to top

Description:


Register a new taxation country for an account.
O1 - Either of these is mandatory



Input Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_CUST_NO_SHORTUnique identifier for account in ProBroker.
O1		IT_CUST_NO_SHORTVarchar(16)
IN_BENEFICIAL_OWNER_IDBeneficial owner Id.
O1		IT_REF_NONumeric(9)
IN_TAX_IDENTIFIER_NUMBERTax Identifier Number.IT_TINVarchar(50)
IN_COUNTRY_CODE_TAX
XMandatory
Tax Country.IT_ISO_COUNTRYVarchar(3)
IN_TAXID_TYPE_IDTaxId type Id
Valid values:
1 - TIN
2 - GIIN.
Default value will be TIN, if this parameter is not provided.		IT_NO9Numeric(9)
IN_IS_DEFAULT_COUNTRYIs default country
Valid values:
0 - False
1 - True.
If this is the only taxation country assigned to the account, it will be added as default taxation country irrespective of, whether the parameter is provided or not, or the value provided.
If this parameter is not provided and the account has taxation country already assigned, the new country will not be added as default.		IT_BOOLVarchar(1)
IN_ACCT_HOLDER_TYPE_IDTax Classification Id.IT_NO9Numeric(9)
IN_TAX_REPORT_TYPETax report type
Valid values :
'0' - None
'1' - FATCA
'2' - CRS.
Value will be retrieved from the country code, if this parameter is not provided		IT_CHAR1Varchar(1)
IN_UNDOCUMENTED_ACCOUNTUndocumented account
Valid values :
0 - False
1 - True.
Default value will be 0, if this parameter is not provided		IT_BOOLVarchar(1)

Output Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type

Customer Requests - BGC Mandate

RQ_ABS_CUST_BGC_MANDATE_NEW

Back to top

Description:


Create a new BGC Mandate for a client.
Note:
Mandate Type:
AN=Account Number, BG=Bankgiro Number.
AN applicable for both natural and juristic persons.
BG applicable only for juristic persons.
Payer Number Indicator:
BG=Bankgiro Number, CI=Civic Number (SSN/Company Number), CU=Customer Number.
BG applicable only if mandate type is BG, i.e. applicable only for juristic persons.
CI applicable only if mandate type is AN, applicable for both natural and juristic persons.
CU applicable only if mandate type is AN, applicable for both natural and juristic persons.



Input Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_CLIENT_NO
XMandatory
Client number.IT_CLIENT_NOVarchar(16)
IN_MANDATE_TYPE
XMandatory
Mandate Type.
Either of 'AN'(Account Number) or 'BG'(Bankgiro Number). See Note for details		IT_CHAR2Varchar(2)
IN_PAYER_NUMBER_INDICATOR
XMandatory
Payer No. Indicator.
Either of 'BG'(Bankgiro Number), 'CI'(Civic Number - SSN/Company Number) or 'CU'(Customer Number). See Note for details		IT_CHAR2Varchar(2)
IN_PAYER_BANK_ACCOUNT
XMandatory
Payer Bank Account.
Applicable and mandatory only if mandate type is AN		IT_NO16Numeric(16)
IN_BANKGIRO_NUMBERBankgiro Number.
Applicable and mandatory only if mandate type is BG		IT_NO10Numeric(10)

Output Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_MANDATE_ID
XMandatory
Unique mandate id.IT_NO12Numeric(12)

Return Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_REQUEST_REFERENCERequest reference.IT_CHAR64Varchar(64)

Instrument requests

RQ_ABS_VP_GET

Back to top

Description:


Get Instrument. Requires one or more of the In parameters to find the instrument. Gets one instrument or a list.
If the request shall return only one instrument there should be searched on IN_INSTRUMENT_ID or IN_VP_NO, IN_TS_EXCH_ID and IN_ISO_CURR (ISIN, stock exchange, currency code).
If IN_VP_NO (ISIN) is used there should normally be only one return, but systems should be prepared for a list return.
Returns a SPRS_LIST if the request returns more than one occurrence.



Input Parameters:

RQ_ABS_VP_NEW

Back to top

Description:


Inserts an instrument in the ProBroker database.
Some fields are defaulted by the default instrument group (VP_GROUP = 99) if omitted in the input.
This request returns a RC_OK and IN_INSTRUMENT_ID which is the unique id of an instrument in ProBroker
O1 - One of there are mandatory

RQ_ABS_VP_GET_DEFAULT_SETTLEMENT_DATE

Back to top

Description:


Get the correct settlement date according to ProBrokers calendar, meaning counting only workdays.
If instrument_id is input the instruments calendar and number of settlement days is used. If not the default calendar (to the legal entity) is used and 3 days is added.
If trade_date is entered the calculation will use the input, if not the todays system date is used as base for calculating the settlement date.



Input Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_TRADE_DATETrade Date.IT_DATEVarchar(8)
IN_INSTRUMENT_IDUnique identifier for instrument in ProBroker.IT_CHAR16Varchar(16)

Output Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_SETTLEMENT_DATE
XMandatory
Settlement Date.IT_DATEVarchar(8)

Return Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_REQUEST_REFERENCERequest reference.IT_CHAR64Varchar(64)
IN_ERROR_CODEError code.IT_NO5Numeric(5)
IN_ERROR_MSGError message.IT_CHAR255Varchar(255)

Order requests

RQ_ABS_ORDR_NEW

Back to top

Description:


Registers a new order. Always returns RC_OK as long as the order is persisted, even if warnings related to Exchange transfer are present.
O1 - One of these is mandatory.
O2 - Any of the set
O3 - Either INSTRUMENT_ID or (VP_NO + TS_EXCH_ID + ISO_CURR) is mandatory
N1 - We recommend to use IN_CUST_LEV_REF_NO or IN_VPS_ACC_NO. N2 - We recommend to use IN_CUSTOMER_CASH_ACCOUNT_ID or IN_CASH_ACCOUNT. It is possible to use the request RQ_CUST_GET_CASH_ACCOUNT_FROM_ACC_NO to convert IN_ACC_NO to the recommended items.
Additionally we can use input parameter IN_PAYMENT_AGENT along with IN_CASH_ACCOUNT to find a specific cash account. If the cash account/payment_agent already exists on the customer the existing cash_account_id should be used. If the combination of cash account and payment agent does not exists, and abstra.ini setting 'CreateAdHocCustCashAccount=1', then a new cash account will be inserted with the specified payment agent.
N3 - If Order Identifiers are to be sent, the Record Descriptor and fields it contains need to be grouped together using the item IN_SEPARATOR.
E.g.
IN_SEPARATOR (value = ORDERIDENTIFIERS)
Record Descriptor and fields
IN_SEPARATOR (value = _GROUP_END_)
N4 - Output parameters to be used by SF (Security Finance) coverage control when module setting SECURITY_FINANCE_COVERAGE_CONTROL is turned on and the SF coverage control return breach in either equity, collateral, capital or exposure.

RQ_ABS_ORDR_AMEND

Back to top

Description:


Amends the specified order.
When using ORDR_AMEND on a stop-loss order with exchange status B/O or B/I, the order must be withdrawn manually and then amended.
IN_PRICE_LIMIT, IN_TS_EXCH_LIMIT is set to zero if TS_ORDER_METHOD = 'M'
If IN_TS_ORDER_VALIDITY_MODE has value 'T' (date) IN_TS_EXPIRY_DATE is mandatory.
If IN_TS_ORDER_VALIDITY_MODE has value 'H' (time) IN_TS_EXPIRY_TIME is mandatory.
If IN_TS_ORDER_VALIDITY_MODE has value 'Y' (period) IN_TS_ORDER_VALIDITY_PERIOD is mandatory
O11, O12, O13, O14 - Use one of the sets.
N1 - If Order Identifiers are to be sent, the Record Descriptor and fields it contains need to be grouped together using the item IN_SEPARATOR.
E.g.
IN_SEPARATOR (value = ORDERIDENTIFIERS)
Record Descriptor and fields
IN_SEPARATOR (value = _GROUP_END_)
N2 - Output parameters to be used by SF (Security Finance) coverage control when module setting SECURITY_FINANCE_COVERAGE_CONTROL is turned on and the SF coverage control return breach in either equity, collateral, capital or exposure.

RQ_ABS_ORDR_CANCEL

Back to top

Description:


Cancels the specified order. If cancellation is succesful and no part of the order is matched, the new order status will be 'K'. If the order is partly matched the request returns order status 'S', NO_NOM_VALUE is reduced by ORDR_REST. ORDR_REST is set to 0.

Order requests - coverage control and validation

RQ_ABS_PORT_CHECK_LEDGER_COVERAGE

Back to top

Description:


Asks for coverage on the ledger. On BUY orders the request checks on ledger minus active buy orders plus customer credit.
Coverage is calculated as:
Sum margin = (IN_MARGIN + IN_MARGIN_LOAN_AMOUNT) - IN_ACCUMULATED_INT.
Available amount = IN_BALANCE + IN_CREDIT_AMOUNT + IN_ACCT_AMOUNT + Sum margin - IN_UNSETTLED_AMOUNT + IN_ATTACHED_QUANTITY_AMOUNT.
If performing gross coverage control the following items must be present: IN_NO_NOM_VALUE, IN_PRICE_LIMIT, IN_ISO_CURR, IN_INSTRUMENT_ID.
Coverage verification in futures through Abstra requires amount to be defined as commission + trade fees for gross balance coverage control



Input Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_COVERAGE_AMOUNT
XMandatory
Amount insurance.coverage.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_CUST_NO_SHORTUnique identifier for account in ProBroker.IT_CUST_NO_SHORTVarchar(16)
IN_PORTFOLIO_IDAccount Id.IT_CHAR16Varchar(16)
IN_SETTLEMENT_CCYSettlement Currency. Defined by ISO-4217.IT_ISO_CURRVarchar(3)
IN_BALANCEClosing balance.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_NO_NOM_VALUEQuantity.IT_NO_NOM_VALUENumeric(20,8)
IN_PRICE_LIMITPrice limit.IT_RATE_24_8Numeric(24,8)
IN_INSTRUMENT_IDUnique identifier for instrument in ProBroker.IT_CHAR16Varchar(16)
IN_ISO_CURRThree letter currency code. Defined by ISO-4217.IT_ISO_CURRVarchar(3)

RQ_ABS_PORT_CHECK_POS_COVERAGE

Back to top

Description:


This is a request that asks for coverage on the portfolio. On SALE orders the request checks on portfolio minus active sales orders.
If general setting USE_CUST_DEPOT = '1' this request checks coverage against depot.
If gross coverage control should be performed limt and settlement currency must be sent with the request.
Coverage verification in futures through Abstra requires amount to be defined as commission + trade fees for gross balance coverage control

RQ_ABS_PBABAL_AVAILABLE_BALANCE

Back to top

Description:


Checks if a reservation is ok in the bank system.
If '0' is entered in the input parameter IN_AMOUNT, the request returns the available balance received from the bank system in IN_AMOUNT. Otherwise it returns a message to confirm success or failure.
The mandatory behaviour of input parameters IN_AMOUNT and IN_EST_AMOUNT is client specific.

RQ_ABS_ORDR_NEW_VALIDATE

Back to top

Description:


Verifies an order prior to registration. Will return error code and error message indicating cause if validation did not pass.
If FillAny is the desired method option don't fill IN_TS_FILL_MODE or IN_TS_IMMEDIATE_WITHDRAW.
If FillAndKill is the desired method option IN_TS_FILL_MODE should have value 'Z' and IN_TS_IMMEDIATE_WITHDRAW value '1'.
If FillOrKill is the desired method option IN_TS_FILL_MODE should have value 'A' and IN_TS_IMMEDIATE_WITHDRAW value '1'.
If AllOrNone is the desired method option IN_TS_FILL_MODE should have value 'A' and IN_TS_IMMEDIATE_WITHDRAW value '0'.
O1 - One of these is mandatory.
O2 - One of these is mandatory.

RQ_ABS_ORDR_CHECK_TRADE_DATE

Back to top

Description:


Checks valid trade date. Uses calendars to verify valid trade, therefore important to keep these calendars correct.
If request is sent with a date which is valid on the selected exchange, the same date will be retuned. If not valid next trade date will be returned.
If instrument id is received, the correct calendar for this instrument will be used. Otherwise the calendar set to be default calendar for the exchange is used.



Input Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_TS_EXCH_ID
XMandatory
Exchange Identifier. Defined by ISO-10383 Market Identifier Code.IT_TS_EXCH_IDVarchar(12)
IN_TRADE_DATE
XMandatory
Trade date to validate.IT_DATEVarchar(8)
IN_INSTRUMENT_IDUnique identifier for instrument in ProBroker.IT_CHAR16Varchar(16)

Output Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_TRADE_DATEValid trade date. If before closing time on selected exchange it will return current date.IT_DATEVarchar(8)

Return Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_REQUEST_REFERENCERequest reference.IT_CHAR64Varchar(64)
IN_ERROR_CODEError code.IT_NO5Numeric(5)
IN_ERROR_MSGError message.IT_CHAR255Varchar(255)

RQ_ABS_ORDR_MANUAL_EXECUTION

Back to top

Description:


Generates contract notes based on specified information. Both part and counter part information must be specified. Use transaction code '7' for contract opening, and '8' for contract closing.
N1 - We recommend to use IN_CUST_LEV_REF_NO or IN_VPS_ACC_NO. N2 - We recommend to use IN_CUSTOMER_CASH_ACCOUNT_ID or IN_CASH_ACCOUNT. It is possible to use the request RQ_CUST_GET_CASH_ACCOUNT_FROM_ACC_NO to convert IN_ACC_NO to the recommended items.
Additionally we can use input parameter IN_PAYMENT_AGENT along with IN_CASH_ACCOUNT to find a specific cash account. If the cash account/payment_agent already exists on the customer the existing cash_account_id should be used. If the combination of cash account and payment agent does not exists, and abstra.ini setting 'CreateAdHocCustCashAccount=1', then a new cash account will be inserted with the specified payment agent.
N3 - If the request execution return warning with message "Instrument risk level is too high, you need to change advise type or specify reason for investment advise", it can be overridden by passing IN_EXECUTION_ONLY with value 1 or pass investment advice parameters as shown below:
IN_SEPARATOR = "INVESTMENT_ADVICE"
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_TYPE
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_REASON_ID
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_COMMENT_ID
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_DISPATCHED_BY_CODE
IN_DESCRIPTION
IN_SEPARATOR = "_GROUP_END_"
NOTE: Investment advice will be created for each order(leg) for which investment advice parameters are passed. Out of the investment advice parameters mentioned above inside IN_SEPARATOR = "INVESTMENT_ADVICE", IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_TYPE and IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_REASON_ID are required

RQ_ABS_ORDR_MANUAL_CONTRACT_NOTE_ORDER_NEW_VALIDATE

Back to top

Description:


Verifies a manual contract note order prior to registration. Will return error code and error message indicating cause if validation did not pass.
N1 - If the request execution throws warning with message "Instrument risk level is too high, you need to change advise type or specify reason for investment advise", it can be overridden by passing IN_EXECUTION_ONLY with value 1 or pass investment advice parameters as shown below:
IN_SEPARATOR = "INVESTMENT_ADVICE"
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_TYPE
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_REASON_ID
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_COMMENT_ID
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_DISPATCHED_BY_CODE
IN_DESCRIPTION
IN_SEPARATOR = "_GROUP_END_"
NOTE: Investment advice will NOT be created in this request even if investment advice parameters are passed. This request will make sure that after passing required parameters for investment advice creation, risk class level warning message mentioned above will not be thrown. Out of the investment advice parameters mentioned above inside IN_SEPARATOR = "INVESTMENT_ADVICE", IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_TYPE and IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_REASON_ID are required.
N2 - If investment advice parameters are provided as an input to this request (as mentioned in the point 1 above), after successful execution of the request the investment avice input parameters will be returned as it is inside IN_SEPARATOR as shown below:
IN_SEPARATOR = "INVESTMENT_ADVICE"
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_TYPE
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_REASON_ID
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_COMMENT_ID
IN_INVESTMENT_ADVICE_DISPATCHED_BY_CODE
IN_DESCRIPTION
IN_SEPARATOR = "_GROUP_END_"

RQ_ABS_PORT_GET_POSITION

Back to top

Description:


Gets the customer's total portfolio from first date this year and to day date. Returns a list with a row for each instrument the customer has a portofolio in. The list will contain instruments that have the given instrument_id as underlying + the instrument, if the search was specified with cust_no_short and instrument_id.
Returns all the records with customers and their position for the specified instrument when only IN_INSTRUMENT_ID is sent as input. The realized profit/loss on fund transactions from ProInvest is shown based on 'GENERAL' system setting 'SHOW_REALIZED_PL_ON_FUNDS'.
O1 - One of these is mandatory.
R - In record Descriptor

RQ_ABS_PORT_GET_POSITION_WITH_ATTACHMENTS

Back to top

Description:


Gets the customer's total portfolio (at date to). It is the same as RQ_ABS_PORT_GET_POSITION, but also returns the fills on the active orders (orders that have not been matched). Returns a list with a row for each instrument the customer has a portofolio in. Returns IN_POSITION = position including attachments on active orders, IN_ATTACHED_QUANTITY = attached quantity on active orders and IN_MEAN_RATE = Mean rate on the attachments.
O1 - One of these is mandatory

RQ_ABS_PORT_SEC_FIN_ACCOUNT

Back to top

Description:


Gets key values, Orders, currencies, FX forwards, external margins and positions for one security finance account. Response is 2 part, one summary and group part, and one record descriptor part for all the positions. If the request contains IN_PARAMATER = 1 the response is exactly as defined under, with all IN_SEPERATOR fields. If IN_PARAMETER is not in the request or something else than '1' all IN_SEPARATOR fields are skipped, and only the fields under SFHEADER is added in addition to RecordDescriptor part.
R - In record descriptor
I - Can be repeted X number of times

Possible output record is in following format
IN_SEPARATOR : 'SFHEADER'
IN_CUST_COMMENT : : Not in use
IN_SF_EQUITY : : Equity (SUM)
IN_SF_COLLATERAL : : Collateral(SUM)
IN_SF_CAPITAL : : Capital(SUM)
IN_SF_EXPOSURE : : Exposure(SUM)
IN_MARKET_VALUE : : Market Value
IN_MARKET_VALUE_ACTIVE : : Active market value for Norwegian pension accounts.
IN_MARKET_VALUE_PASSIVE : : Passive market value for Norwegian pension accounts.
IN_SF_MARGIN_VALUE : : Margin Value
IN_CREDIT_LIMIT : : Credit Limit
IN_SF_CREDIT_LIMIT_EXTRA : : Credit Extra
IN_SF_EXPOSURE_LIMIT : : Exposure Limit
IN_SF_LEDGER_BALANCE : : Ledger Balance
IN_RESERVED_WITHDRAWALS : : Reserved Withdrawals
IN_SF_BANK_BALANCE : : Bank Balance
IN_ACCRUED_INTEREST : : Accrued Interest

RQ_ABS_PORT_ASK_PORTFOLIO_TRANSFER

Back to top

Description:


The purpose of the request is to transfer the portfolio of ASK to another single or multiple ASK. It is possible to transfer ledger balance as well as instrument's position using this request.
If TAXSRVR setting TAX_GROUPING_LEVEL is 1 i.e. Account, then ledger balance and positions to be transferred, of single account can be provided in the request.
If TAX_GROUPING_LEVEL is 2 i.e. Client, then it is possible to provide ledger balance and positions to be transferred, of multiple ASK accounts of the same client.

X - Mandatory Parameter.
O1 - Any of the parameter mandatory
Either INSTRUMENT_ID or (VP_NO + TS_EXCH_ID + ISO_CURR) is mandatory
R - Record descriptor

Possible inputs parameter combinations
N1 : If LEDGER ASK portfolio transfer
IN_SEPARATOR : Value should be 'LEDGER'
IN_ACCT_DATE : General ledger date
IN_ACCT_VAL_DATE : Value date (settlement date)
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR : X : Record descriptor for the ledger group records
IN_CUST_NO_SHORT : R,X : Account number to move from
IN_TR_CUST_NO_SHORT : R,X : Client account to move to
IN_ISO_CURR : R,X : Ledger balance currency
IN_ACCT_AMOUNT : R,X : Amount to be transferred
IN_VAL_RATE : R,X : Exchange rate. It should be the IN_VAL_RATE received in the response of RQ_ABS_TAX_ACCOUNT_BALANCE_LIST.
IN_ENTRY_BASIS_TYPE : R : Entry Basis Type
IN_ACCT_COMMENT : R : Comment
IN_SEPARATOR : _GROUP_END_

N2 : If POSITION ASK portfolio transfer
IN_SEPARATOR : Value should be 'POSITION'
IN_TRADE_DATE : Trade date. Year from this date will be used as tax year and tax values will be fetched using this year.
IN_SETTLEMENT_DATE : Settlement date
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR : X : Record descriptor for the positions group records
IN_CUST_NO_SHORT : R,X : Account number to move from
IN_TR_CUST_NO_SHORT : R,X : Client account to move to
IN_INSTRUMENT_ID : R,X : Instrument Id
IN_NO_NOM_VALUE : R,O1 : Position to be transported
IN_TRADE_PRICE : R,X : Trade price. It should be market price (IN_MARKET_PRICE) received from Abstra request RQ_ABS_PORT_LIST_TRANSFER_POSITIONS. Not applicable for fund instrument.
IN_AMOUNT : R,O1 : It is applicable only if instrument is of type Fund.
IN_VAL_RATE : R,X : Exchange rate from position
IN_CUST_LEV_REF_NO : R : Delivery information id for clearing. Only applicable when clearing is implemented.
IN_TR_CUST_LEV_REF_NO : R : Delivery information id for clearing. Only applicable when clearing is implemented.
IN_EXTERNAL_TRANSPORT : R : Transfer without any manual portfolio transaction in ProBroker for receiving safe account.
IN_ENTRY_BASIS_TYPE : R : Entry basis type. Require predefined entry basis types in ProBroker.
IN_INTERNAL_COMMENT : R : Internal comment on the manual portfolio transaction
IN_TRANS_COMMENT : R : External comment on the manual portfolio transaction
IN_SEPARATOR : _GROUP_END_

IN_EXTRENAL_TRANSPORT value denotes:
0=With manual portfolio transaction
1=Without manual portfolio transaction

Possible output record parameter combinations
IN_SEPARATOR : Value should be 'LEDGER'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR : X
IN_CUST_NO_SHORT : R,X : Account number to move from
IN_TR_CUST_NO_SHORT : R,X : Client account to move to
IN_ISO_CURR : R,X : Instrument Id
IN_PURCHASE_AMOUNT : R,X : Purchase amount
IN_RECORD_ERROR_CODE : R,X
IN_RECORD_ERROR_MSG : R,X
IN_SEPARATOR : _GROUP_END_

IN_SEPARATOR : Value should be 'POSITION'
IN_RECORD_DESCRIPTOR : X
IN_CUST_NO_SHORT : R,X : Account number to move from
IN_TR_CUST_NO_SHORT : R,X : Client account to move to
IN_INSTRUMENT_ID : R,X : Instrument Id
IN_PURCHASE_AMOUNT : R,X : Purchase amount
IN_EXECUTED : R,X : Executed, 0=No, 1=Yes.
IN_MESSAGE_TEXT : R,X : Message text from the underlying implementation of position transfer if an error occur. Recommened to use IN_RECORD_ERROR_MSG.
IN_RECORD_ERROR_CODE : R,X
IN_RECORD_ERROR_MSG : R,X
IN_SEPARATOR : _GROUP_END_



Input Parameters:

RQ_ABS_PORT_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ACCOUNT_LIST

Back to top

Description:


Lists account having a position for the specified period of a notification event.

Note:
To get the list of accounts of an event having accounts delivery status as 'NotDelivered,
the position is not 0 and has either e-address or postal address registered for SRDII dispatch,
user needs to set the IN_IS_DISPATCHABLE to true.

E-address exist field is returned as true for accounts with report type SRD II and channel type
E-mail or Telefax. Similarly, the postal address exist field is returned as true for an account with report type SRD II and channel type Print.

RQ_ABS_ORDR_MODEL_PORTFOLIO_INVESTMENT_REBALANCE

Back to top

Description:


Re-balance the model portfolio investment as per the weights of each instrument in the corresponding model portfolio. If IN_CUST_NO_SHORT is provided in the input, then the portfolio of only that customer will be re-balanced as per the currently connected model portfolio.
IN_CASH_ACCOUNT is allowed only if model portfolio investment re-balance request is for a specific customer and order aggregation is not enabled.
O1 = One of these is mandatory.
If IN_MODEL_PORTFOLIO_ID is provided in the input, then portfolio of all the clients connected to the specified model portfolio will be re-balanced.

Back to top

Description:


Comment:
Lists the TWR and market values for given customer.

default grouping level will be "Account" or "Client" according to input parameter.
If input has IN_CUST_NO_SHORT, then grouping level will be considered as Account.
If input has IN_CLIENT_NO, then grouping level will be considered as Client

Description:


Lists the market values, balance movement and TWR for the given model portfolio. Also, it returns the same values in instrument currency if the grouping level is ModelPortfolioInstrumentId or ModelPortfolioCurrency. Comment:
In this request, if IN_GROUPING_LEVEL_NAME is not provided in the request, then grouping level is set to ModelPortfolio by default



Input Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_MODEL_PORTFOLIO_ID
XMandatory
Unique id of model portfolio in ProBroker.IT_REF_NONumeric(9)
IN_DATE_FROM
XMandatory
Valid From.IT_DATEVarchar(8)
IN_DATE_TO
XMandatory
Valid To.IT_DATEVarchar(8)
IN_GROUPING_LEVEL_NAMEGrouping level name. Valid values are as follows:
1. ModelPortfolio (Grouping fields: IN_MODEL_PORTFOLIO_ID)
2. ModelPortfolioCountry (Grouping fields: IN_MODEL_PORTFOLIO_ID, IN_COUNTRY_CODE)
3. ModelPortfolioCurrency (Grouping fields: IN_MODEL_PORTFOLIO_ID, IN_ISO_CURR)
4. ModelPortfolioIndustry (Grouping fields: IN_MODEL_PORTFOLIO_ID, IN_VP_TYPE, IN_VP_GROUP)
5. ModelPortfolioInstrumentId (Grouping fields: IN_MODEL_PORTFOLIO_ID, IN_INSTRUMENT_ID)
6. ModelPortfolioSector (Grouping fields: IN_MODEL_PORTFOLIO_ID, IN_VP_TYPE).		IT_CHAR64Varchar(64)
IN_PERIOD_TYPEIt specifies the type of period. The valid values of this field are as follows:
1. D (For day)
2. W (For week)
3. M (For month)
4. Y (For year)
Default value of this field will be D.		IT_CHAR1Varchar(1)
IN_PERIOD_COUNTSCount of the specified period type. Default value will be 1. For example, if value of this field is 2 and
IN_PERIOD_TYPE is W, then a period length will be of 2 weeks. It should be between 1 and 99.		IT_NO4Numeric(4)
IN_SETTLEMENT_CCYCurrency in which market value, balance movement and TWR have to be calculated.IT_ISO_CURRVarchar(3)
IN_RETURNS_CALCULATION_METHODMethod to be used to calculate portfolio returns.
0 True Time weighted return (Default)
1 Modified Dietz.		IT_NO1Numeric(1)

RQ_ABS_PERF_FUND_NET_ASSET_VALUE_CALCULATE

Back to top

Description:


Gets the net asset value of a specified fund on specified date. It also returns all the values used for calculation of net asset value.
Comment:
It is required to enable module 'FUND_NAV' and user needs to have 'FUND_NAV_VIEW' or 'FUND_NAV_MAINTENANCE' authorization to get the net asset value of a fund



Input Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_INSTRUMENT_IDUnique identifier for instrument in ProBroker.IT_CHAR16Varchar(16)
IN_VP_NOInternational Securities Identification Numbering (ISIN). Defined by ISO-6166.IT_ISIN_NOVarchar(12)
IN_NET_ASSET_VALUE_DATENet Asset Value Date. If it is not provided, then default will be system date.IT_DATEVarchar(8)
IN_DO_SAVE0/1 flags indicating whether calculated NAV should be stored in database or not. If it is 1, then user needs to have 'FUND_NAV_MAINTENANCE' authorization..IT_BOOLVarchar(1)

Output Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_TRADE_VOLUME
XMandatory
Total Traded Amount of the units of underlying instruments in the fund portfolio.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_BROKERAGE
XMandatory
Total Brokerage on the traded amount.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_TRADE_TOTAL
XMandatory
Total cost of units of underlying instruments in the portfolio including brokerage i.e. IN_TRADE_VOLUME + IN_BROKERAGE.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_UNREALIZED_PROFIT_LOSS
XMandatory
Difference between market value of portfolio excluding accrued interest and portfolio cost.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_ACCRUED_INTEREST
XMandatory
Accrued Interest if there is a bond instrument in the portfolio.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_MARKET_VALUE
XMandatory
Total Market Value of the positions.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_SETTLED_AMOUNT
XMandatory
Settled Amount.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_UNSETTLED_AMOUNT
XMandatory
Unsettled Amount.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_SUM_ACCT_AMOUNT
XMandatory
Ledger balance including unsettled amount.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_SUM_BALANCE
XMandatory
Bank Balance.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_INTEREST
XMandatory
Interest on ledger balance.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_RECEIVABLES
XMandatory
Receivable amount from selling of underlying instruments shares/units.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_CUSTOMER_RECEIVABLES
XMandatory
Receivable Amount from investors.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_LIABILITIES
XMandatory
Payable amount for buying of underlying instruments shares/units.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_CUSTOMER_LIABILITIES
XMandatory
Payable Amount to the investors.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_CASH_AMOUNT
XMandatory
Ledger Balance + Bank Balance + Interest + Receivable + Other Receivable - liabilities - other liabilities.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_FUND_MANAGEMENT_AMOUNT
XMandatory
Fund Management Fee on given NAV date.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_ACCRUED_FUND_MANAGEMENT_AMOUNT
XMandatory
Accrued Fund Management Amount.IT_AMOUNTNumeric(14,2)
IN_TOTAL_FUND_VALUE
XMandatory
Total Value of the Fund Portfolio i.e. Market Value of positions + Total Cash - Accrued Fund Management Fee.IT_AMOUNT_20_4Numeric(20,4)
IN_SHARE_COUNT
XMandatory
Share count.IT_NO_NOM_VALUENumeric(20,8)
IN_NET_ASSET_VALUE
XMandatory
Net Asset Value per unit of the fund i.e. Total Fund Value / Total Fund Units.IT_FUND_PRICENumeric(12,6)
IN_SUBSCR_PRICE
XMandatory
Fund`s Subscription Price. This is same as NAV.IT_FUND_PRICENumeric(12,6)
IN_REDMP_PRICE
XMandatory
Fund`s Redemption Price. This is same as NAV.IT_FUND_PRICENumeric(12,6)

Return Parameters:

Field NameMDescriptionProBroker TypeData Type
IN_REQUEST_REFERENCERequest reference.IT_CHAR64Varchar(64)
IN_ERROR_CODEError code.IT_NO5Numeric(5)
IN_ERROR_MSGError message.IT_CHAR255Varchar(255)
